1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
Lighting is decided from drawings and catalogs,
but homeowners cannot easily imagine how it will actually look.

2
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:20,000
If something feels wrong after construction,
moving a fixture costs real money.

3
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:35,000
Lighting Lab lets homeowners try lighting plans in their own floor plan
and check the atmosphere before construction—no CAD skills needed.

4
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:50,000
In this house, we are still deciding the dining lighting.
I select the pendant over the table.

5
00:00:50,000 --> 00:01:10,000
First, color temperature: from a warm 2700K up to 3500K.
Then brightness, and a different position over the table.

6
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:30,000
In 3D, I can check how the table and its surroundings actually look.
Realistic mode includes indirect light for the whole-room atmosphere.

7
00:01:30,000 --> 00:02:05,000
Another position, a different spread of light, one more color temperature.
Lighting Lab lets you explore until the lighting fits the way you live.

8
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:23,000
2D and 3D stay in sync. Each fixture exposes brightness,
color temperature, and beam angle—on PC and on a phone.

9
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:50,000
Codex with GPT-5.6 critically reviewed realism and mobile performance,
and this session delivered mobile improvements, English, tests, and the public release.

10
00:02:50,000 --> 00:03:00,000
Quickly try lighting layouts, brightness, and color temperature
in your own floor plan—before construction.
